The Biden-Harris Administration recently held a meeting with leadership and experts from national associations and organizations responsible for protecting older adults and ensuring quality care in long-term care facilities. The meeting focused on the availability of vaccines for flu, RSV, and COVID-19 during the fall and winter season, and the importance of vaccination as the best protection against these viruses. The participants discussed challenges such as workforce shortages and improving communication about accessing federal resources. They also shared best practices and challenges in increasing vaccination access, ensuring access to tests, building trust in vaccines, and improving education and training for frontline staff. The Administration officials expressed gratitude for the efforts of the leaders and committed to ongoing discussions to address concerns and track progress.